snippet.textDisplay:
There are many comments which basically say two things, 'Rohail Hayat' and 'songs being different from some 'perfect' coke studio' which existed at some point. I think it's good to be a critic but it would be good to mention what's wrong with these writings/compositions and I personally would like hear more about content then just one comment which in the end means nothing. 

Also I don't have data so I am not sure but I think in the last three seasons we have seen many songs totally written for Coke Studio. This is great to produce new songs, more new singers, more new music directors. more diversity and more team work. 

I personally liked season 2,3 and think there was not much going on in season 4-5 and then so much experimentation in 6. I think last two seasons were good with new content and diversity and also bringing innovation and new ideas after 7 seasons. It's not easy to bring fresh music after so many seasons.. and it's still going strong.. I was a fan of Rohail Hayat and I am fan of Strings. So much talent we have. Coke Studio is one of the best things from Pakistan to introduce to my International friends.

snippet.textDisplay:
Meesha Shafi never disappoints, such a diva... I love her swagger and arrogance in the video, fitting of a rock star!
There's so much versatility and depth in her voice, she has given us energetic hits (Sun Ve Balori) and soulful hits (Dasht-e-Tanhai) alike...
A good composition brings together the vocals and instruments in a good sync and they blend in well in this song for my liking! Love it, thank you Meesha and Coke Studio! Haters please move on...
